title: U.S. automobile registrations 1999 to 2017
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Number of passenger cars. In total the number of data points it has is 4.
In general Number of passenger cars has fallen over the Year.
Number of passenger cars is slightly decreasing from 1999 to 2017.
The most drastic decrease took place within the Year 2011 and 2017.
The highest Number of passenger cars, of value 136568083.0 was reached at Year 2005
The lowest Number of passenger cars, of value 111177029.0 was reported at Year 2017
